goals.question: What is the distribution of airports across different states in the US?
goals.visualization: choropleth map of the US with the number of airports per state
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which states have the highest and lowest number of airports, and identify any patterns or trends in airport distribution across the country.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airports across different cities in the US?
goals.visualization: bar chart of the top 10 cities with the highest number of airports
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify which cities have the highest concentration of airports, and whether there are any cities with significantly more airports than others.

goals.question: What is the distribution of latitude and longitude of airports in the US?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude and longitude of all airports
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any clusters or patterns in the distribution of airports across the US, and whether there are any regions with significantly more or fewer airports than others.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airport names in the US?
goals.visualization: word cloud of the most common airport names
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the most common names of airports in the US, and whether there are any patterns or trends in airport naming conventions.

goals.question: What is the distribution of IATA codes across different airports in the US?
goals.visualization: histogram of the number of airports per IATA code
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify which IATA codes are used most frequently in the US, and whether there are any codes that are significantly more common than others.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Read US states shapefile
    us_states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json")

    # Group data by state and count airports
    state_counts = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='count')

    # Merge state_counts with us_states GeoDataFrame
    merged_data = us_states.merge(state_counts, left_on='name', right_on='state')

    # Create choropleth map
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 25))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    merged_data.plot(column='count', cmap='coolwarm', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True, cax=cax)

    # Set title
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports across different states in the US?", wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_airport_count = data['city'].value_counts().head(10)
    city_airport_count.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports across different cities in the US?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Number of Airports'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude of airports in the US?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Prepare the text for the word cloud
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])

    # Create the word cloud
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate(text)

    # Plot the word cloud
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names in the US?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    iata_counts = data['iata'].value_counts()
    plt.hist(iata_counts, bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Airports per IATA Code')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of IATA codes across different airports in the US?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['IATA Code Distribution'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
